{title: For All the Saints}
{subtitle: William W. How, 1864 — Vaughan Williams "Sine Nomine" tune, 1906}
{key: G}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 88}
{comment: All Saints' Day hymn. The "Sine Nomine" tune ("without a name") is one of the finest English hymn tunes of the 20th century.}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[G]For all the [D]saints, who [Em]from their [C]labors [G]rest
[G]Who Thee by [D]faith be[C]fore the [G]world con[D]fessed
[G]Thy name, O [Em]Jesus, [C]be for[D]ever [G]blest
[C]Alle[D]lu[G]ia, Alle[D]lu[G]ia!
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
